From 64a68158738ec8f520347144352f7a09bdb9e169 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harshit Mogalapalli <harshit.m.mogalapalli@oracle.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Jan 2023 07:36:09 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] iio: accel: mma9551_core: Prevent uninitialized variable in mma9551_read_config_word()
Git-commit: 64a68158738ec8f520347144352f7a09bdb9e169
Patch-mainline: v6.3-rc1
References: git-fixes

Smatch Warns:
drivers/iio/accel/mma9551_core.c:299
	mma9551_read_config_word() error: uninitialized symbol 'v'.

When (offset >= 1 << 12) is true mma9551_transfer() will return -EINVAL
without 'v' being initialized, so check for the error and return.

Note: No actual bug as caller checks the return value and does not
use the parameter in the problem case.

Signed-off-by: Harshit Mogalapalli <harshit.m.mogalapalli@oracle.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230126153610.3586243-1-harshit.m.mogalapalli@oracle.com
Signed-off-by: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/iio/accel/mma9551_core.c |    5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/iio/accel/mma9551_core.c
+++ b/drivers/iio/accel/mma9551_core.c
@@ -296,9 +296,12 @@ int mma9551_read_config_word(struct i2c_
 
 	ret = mma9551_transfer(client, app_id, MMA9551_CMD_READ_CONFIG,
 			       reg, NULL, 0, (u8 *)&v, 2);
+	if (ret < 0)
+		return ret;
+
 	*val = be16_to_cpu(v);
 
-	return ret;
+	return 0;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(mma9551_read_config_word);
 
